doc.after: Cimbrian German Zimbrisch or Tzimbrisch Italian Cimbro refers to any of several local Upper German varieties spoken in northeastern Italy The speakers of the language are known as Zimbern  Cimbrian is a Germanic language related to Bavarian and most probably deriving from a Southern Bavarian dialect although a Lombardic origin cannot be ruled out It is also related to the M cheno language Its many essential differences in grammar as well as in vocabulary and pronunciation make it practically unintelligible for people speaking Standard German or Bavarian Bavarian is also spoken in the province of South Tyrol The impact of the surrounding varieties of Italian on Cimbrian has been very strong
